<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="126" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,310,1241,1267]" box="[189,310,1241,1267]" pageId="20" pageNumber="126">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1241,1267]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="126" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1241,1267]" pageId="20" pageNumber="126">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,1399,1288,1421]" pageId="20" pageNumber="126">
Eyes pilose (
<figureCitation box="[349,441,1288,1314]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="26.[189,232,1882,1908]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,597,1846]" captionTargetId="figure-82@26.[189,1399,596,1846]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Fig. 14. Head, ♀, dorsal view (A, C, E, G) and lateral view (B, D, F, H). A–B. Eumerus brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., paratype (HMIM). C–D. E. coeruleus (Becker, 1913), Ghoochan, Iran (HMIM). E–F. E. longitarsis Peck, 1979, Mian Jangal, Iran (JSA). G–H. E. persarum Stackelberg, 1961, Bazman, Iran (JSA). Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239361" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239361/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="126">Figs 14</figureCitation>
E–F, 15H), about 1 ommatidium spaced in males (
<figureCitation box="[1075,1189,1288,1315]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="27.[189,232,1882,1908]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,651,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-70@27.[190,1400,651,1845]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Fig. 15. Head, ♂, dorsal view (A, C, E, G) and lateral view (B, D, F, H). A–B. Eumerus coeruleus (Becker, 1913), Chekab Valley, Iran (JSA). C–D. E. jacobsoni Becker, 1913, Chekab Valley, Iran (JSA). E–F. E. kazanovzkyae Paramonov, 1927, Paveh, Iran (HMIM). G–H. E. longitarsis Peck, 1979, Chekab Valley, Iran (JSA). Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239367/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="126">Fig. 15G</figureCitation>
); ocellar triangle isosceles; scutum and scutellum shiny metallic, weakly pollinose (
<figureCitation box="[992,1089,1323,1350]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1812,1838]" captionTargetBox="[289,1297,265,1777]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[289,1297,265,1777]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Adult habitus, ♂, dorsal view. A. Eumerus atricolorus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). B. E. brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). C. E. falsus Becker, 1922, Chekab Valley, Iran (HMIM). D. E. chekabicus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). E. E. coeruleus (Becker, 1913), Chekab Valley, Iran (JSA). F. E. jacobsoni Becker, 1913, Chekab Valley, Iran (JSA). G. E. kazanovzkyae Paramonov, 1927, abdomen, Paveh, Iran (HMIM). H. E. longitarsis Peck, 1979, Chekab Valley, Iran (JSA). Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239303" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239303/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="126">Fig. 3H</figureCitation>
), covered with white pile (
<figureCitation box="[197,298,1359,1385]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1814,1840]" captionTargetBox="[290,1294,268,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[290,1294,268,1774]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Adult habitus, ♂, lateral view. A. Eumerus atricolorus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). B. E. brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). C. E. falsus Becker, 1922, Chekab Valley, Iran (HMIM). D. E. chekabicus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). E. E. coeruleus (Becker, 1913), Chekab Valley, Iran (JSA). F. E. jacobsoni Becker, 1913, Chekab Valley, Iran (JSA). G. E. kazanovzkyae Paramonov, 1927, Paveh, Iran (HMIM). H. E. longitarsis Peck, 1979, Chekab Valley, Iran (JSA). Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239319" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239319/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="126">Figs 6H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[315,352,1359,1385]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1812,1838]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,336,1746]" captionTargetId="figure-19@15.[189,1399,336,1746]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 8. A–E. Adult habitus, lateral view. F. Basicosta. A–D. Female. E–F. Male. A. Eumerus brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., paratype (HMIM). B. E. coeruleus (Becker, 1913), Ghoochan, Iran (HMIM). C. E. longitarsis Peck, 1979, Mian Jangal, Iran (JSA). D. E. persarum Stackelberg, 1961, Bazman, Iran (JSA). E. E. tricolor (Fabricius, 1798), Paleochori, Greece (JSA). F. E. tadzhikorum Stackelberg, 1949, Chekab Valley, Iran (JSA). Scale bars = 1.0 mm. Abbreviations: ac = anterodorsal costal setae; pc = posterodorsal costal setae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239333" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239333/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="126">8C</figureCitation>
); legs predominantly black; metaleg extremely long and slender; metatibia as long as metafemur; metatarsus distinctly longer than metatibia; abdomen black (
<figureCitation box="[1040,1133,1394,1421]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1916,1942]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,836,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-149@9.[189,1398,836,1873]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Adult habitus, ♀, dorsal view. A. Eumerus brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., paratype (HMIM). B. E. coeruleus (Becker, 1913), Ghoochan, Iran (HMIM). C. E. longitarsis Peck, 1979, Mian Jangal, Iran (JSA). D. E. persarum Stackelberg, 1961, Bazman, Iran (JSA). Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239315" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239315/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="126">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
